parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Front Electronic Module (FEM) can cause a sudden loss of power to the vehicle, resulting in a loss of steering, brakes, and throttle control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
loss of steering
brakes
and throttle control
inability to start the vehicle
failure of hazard lights
windows
door locks
and hood latch
transmission failure warnings
engine warnings
brake lamp control malfunction warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes do not respond or respond slowly
the vehicle does not slow down or stop even when pressing the brake pedal firmly
the ABS brakes do not engage
the vehicle is unable to stop in a safe distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning trunk closure sensor can cause the trunk to close unexpectedly, potentially causing injury to individuals in the area.
symptoms: The trunk closes unexpectedly
even when the sensor is activated accidentally by a foot or an animal
resulting in potential injury to individuals in the area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause injury to the driver and occupants, as well as distract the driver and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes or shatters suddenly
without warning
while driving
potentially causing injury to the driver and occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Loss of Brake Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected acceleration of the vehicle, accompanied by a loss of brake control, can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine revs and races to high RPM
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the brake pedal is unresponsive or fails to slow the vehicle
the vehicle fails to stop or slow down
the vehicle swerves or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
